A holding voltage of −100 mV was applied to macropatches of oocyte membranes to maintain the channels in the resting state. The blocking and unblocking rates were calculated from the time course of the decaying phase of the macroscopic current after a voltage step as previously described by Murrell-Lagnado and Aldrich (1993a
, 1993b
; see also Patton et al., 1993). A steady state level of current remaining after the decay was assumed to be the equilibrium condition between blocking and unblocking of channels by peptide. The currents were fitted with the exponential function: 1\documentclass[10pt]{article}
